						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragmentary stone lying in the compound of the Śaṅkaraliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōvidēva—A.D. 1176.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and mutilated record is dated in the king's regnal <hi rend="bold">year 10, ḍurmati, Chaitra, śu. 5, Wednesday.</hi><note n="202-1">In the record, only the letter<ka>sau</ka> which may stand for ṣaumyavāra, <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Wednesday, is visible.</note>āpparently, the cyclic year ḍurmati is a mistake for ḍurmukhi. The details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1176, ṁarch 17, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription appears to record a gift of land to the temple of Śaṅkaradēva Other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
